hopobject.body: Could I take your name and number, please? baton pharmaceuticals Karl Y. Bilimoria, M.D., from Northwestern University in Chicago, and colleagues examined whether a surveillance bias influences the validity of reported VTE rates using 2010 Hospital Compare and American Hospital Association merged data from 2,838 hospitals. VTE imaging and event rates were calculated using 2009 to 2010 Medicare claims data for 954,926 surgical patient discharges from 2,786 hospitals.
